    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.80a" />
                <note type="curatorial">194 House Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">80</fw>
                
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Dec 5 31</dateline>
                
                
                
                <dateline>Dear Comrade:</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Just a word to say that I'm happy about your Nov. number. The Robinson article is a shrewd and really penetrating bit of criticism, I believe. Fair and kindly, too. It's a bull's eye shot, no doubt.</p>
               
                <p>And the installment of the Sentimental Journey is corkingly good, with the note in it I wanted to hear.</p>
                
                <p>The book has aroused a lot enthusiasm. Macmillans have written me 3 urgent letters, asking to publish it. They heard of it by accident. Amusing.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>With love always,</salute>
                
                <signed>Jno.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
            
            
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.80b"/>
                
                <ab type="return">
                    After 5 days, return to
                    Neihardt
                    ...............................
                    BRANSON, MO.
                </ab>
                
                <ab type="postmark">
                    BRANSON DEC 4 1 -PM 1931 MO.
                </ab>
                
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>2 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNTIED STATES <unclear reason="missing" cert="high">POSTAGE</unclear> 2 CENTS <unclear reason="missing" cert="high">2</unclear></p>
                </figure>
                
                <ab type="address">
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. J.T. House</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>New River State College</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Montgomery,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>West Virginia</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </ab>
                
            </div1>
